<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  Schema: Mesh_function_arm
   <express_ref linkend="mesh_function:arm:Mesh_function_arm"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Mesh_function_arm">
	The mesh functions defined in this application module are interpolation functions defined over a mesh. 
	The mesh may be either structured or unstructured and individual interpolation functions can be defined for each cell of the mesh.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Mesh_function_arm  Entity: Mesh_function  
   <express_ref linkend="mesh_function:arm:Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function">
<p>
	A <b>Mesh_function</b> is an application defined function that:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		has a domain that consists of a table of real tuple spaces;
		<p>
			The table is a one dimensional array for an unstructured mesh, but can be a rectangular array of any dimension for a structured mesh.
		</p>
		<p>
			The real tuples can have different dimensions, if the mesh contains cells of different dimensions. 
		</p>
		<p>
			The real tuple spaces can have different bounds, if the mesh contains cells of different shape, such as wedges and hexhedra.
		</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		has a set of control values, such that the function within each cell is determined by a subset of the control values 
		and basis for that cell.
		<p>
		The assignment of control values to cells is determined by the topology of the mesh.
		</p>
		<p>
			A control value is usually, but not necessarily, the value of the function at a position within the mesh
		</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		interpolates or extrapolates separately within each cell from the control values assigned to that cell.
	</li>
</ul>  
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Mesh_function_arm  Entity: Mesh_function  Attribute: mesh 
   <express_ref linkend="mesh_function:arm:Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function.mesh"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function.mesh">
	the 
	<express_ref linkend="Mesh_topology:arm:Mesh_topology_arm.Mesh"/> 
	for the <b>Mesh_function</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Mesh_function_arm  Entity: Mesh_function  Attribute: basis 
   <express_ref linkend="mesh_function:arm:Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function.basis"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function.basis">
	the 
	<express_ref linkend="Mesh_function:arm:Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function_basis"/> 
	specifying the methods of interpolation or extraction for use within each cell of the 
	<express_ref linkend="Mesh_topology:arm:Mesh_topology_arm.Mesh"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Mesh_function_arm  Entity: Mesh_function  Attribute: uniform 
   <express_ref linkend="mesh_function:arm:Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function.uniform"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function.uniform">
<p>
	a flag which indicates whether or not the the <b>Mesh_function</b> has a uniform basis, as follows:
</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			if <b>uniform</b> is true, then each cell of the mesh has the same 
			<express_ref linkend="Mesh_function:arm:Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function_basis"/>;
		</li>
		<li>
			if <b>uniform</b> is false, then a 
			<express_ref linkend="Mesh_function:arm:Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function_basis"/> 
			is specified separately for each cell of the 
			<express_ref linkend="Mesh_topology:arm:Mesh_topology_arm.Mesh"/>.
		</li>
	</ul>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Mesh_function_arm  Entity: Mesh_function  Attribute: vertex_values 
   <express_ref linkend="mesh_function:arm:Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function.vertex_values"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Mesh_function_arm.Mesh_function.vertex_values">
<p>
	a flag that indicates whether or not the control values are specified for the vertices or the cells of the 
	<express_ref linkend="Mesh_topology:arm:Mesh_topology_arm.Mesh"/>, 
	as follows:
</p>
	<ul>
		<li> 
			if <b>vertex_values</b> is true, then the control values are specified for the array of unique 
			<express_ref linkend="Elemental_topology:arm:Elemental_topology_arm.Vertex"/> 
			for the cells of the 
			<express_ref linkend="Mesh_topology:arm:Mesh_topology_arm.Mesh"/>;
		</li>
		<li>
			if <b>vertex_values</b> is false, then the control values are specified for a separate pattern of discretisation points 
			for each cell of the 
			<express_ref linkend="Mesh_topology:arm:Mesh_topology_arm.Mesh"/>.
		</li>			
	</ul>
</ext_description>

